Gov. Mai Mala Buni today announced the reopening of Gaidam weekly market with immediate effect after it had been shut for about a year following Boko Haram attacks on the commercial hub. The governor made the announcement at Gaidam town while holding a town hall meeting with stakeholders in the local government area. Buni during the meeting also approved the upward review of curfew in the town from 6 pm to 10 pm as well as the recruitment of 150 vigilante members to boost the existing 50 vigilantes who are complementing the troops in clearance operations. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.